column2: Some refactoring for reusing GenerateEquals UI in scala plugin

column3: Please do respect the formatting. We don't put getters in a single line. I'll fix it for you this time, but in the future, as I mentioned, please respect the style of the codebase you're contributing to.

I've also moved AbstractGenerateEqualsWizard to the java-impl module. equals() and hashCode() are JVM-specific concepts, and a wizard to generate those is of no use for IDEs that don't target the JVM.
createMemberSelectionTable() is never invoked through the AbstractMemberSelectionPanel interface, so I've removed it from the interface.
With these remarks, the pull request has been merged and pushed.
Also note that pull requests should normally be created from a specific branch that consists your specific set of changes, not from the master branch.
